description.plain:
“A singer and Grammy-nominated songwriter, Brooklyn, New York native Stacy Barthe is a woman of many talents. Signed to John Legend’s Homeschool label through Motown Records, Barthe has been working behind the scenes, writing for superstars like Rihanna, Miley Cyrus, Alicia Keys, Britney Spears and Katy Perry. Additionally, her vocals can be heard on T.I.’s André 3000-assisted single “Sorry.” – DJ Z for djbooth

An excellent full bio is available on Ms. Barthe’s website.

description.plain:
The 14th track on Stacy’s album ‘Becoming’ and a cover of Anita Baker’s ‘Angel’



https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jzE09bcUCQo

The same song can be found as an interlude on the album ‘Love in the Future’ by John Legend and it also features Stacy Barthe, although it’s a shorter version of the collaboration.

https://genius.com/John-legend-angel-interlude-lyrics
